    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="942"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d942">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3004.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 29, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Referring to our conversation
                    on the 28th instant, when you again urged that this Government take some drastic
                    action in relation to Mr. Vasquez<note n="1" xml:id="d942fn1">Vásquez
                        Gómez.</note> at San Antonio, Texas, it is my duty to inform your excellency
                    that, although the greatest circumspection is being exercised, there has not, up
                    to the present time, been proven on the part of Mr. Vásquez any act which falls
                    within the statutes of the United States.</p>
                <p>I may remark that your excellency will gain a clear idea as to the legal aspects
                    of such cases by referring to the correspondence of the Department with your
                    Embassy during the Madero revolution; for example, the letter of December 1,
                        1910,<note n="2" xml:id="d942fn2">See <ref target="frus1911#pg_370">For.
                            Rel. 1911, pp. 370</ref>–<ref target="frus1911#pg_371">371</ref>.</note>
                    aide-mémoire of January 23, 1911,<note n="3" xml:id="d942fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1911#pg_303">Id., p. 303</ref>.</note> and the letter of
                    June 7, 1911.<note n="4" xml:id="d942fn4">
                        <ref target="frus1911#pg_501">Id., pp. 501</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1911#pg_502">502</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
